<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="T" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Tun" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Tun,</orth> 1) a large cask: <cit><quote>a t. of man is thy companion,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.493" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 4, 493</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>sends you . . . this t. of treasure,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 1.2.255" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 I, 2, 255</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>--s of blood,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 4.5.105" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. IV, 5, 105</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) a certain measure: <cit><quote>with so many --s of oil in his belly,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.1.65" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. II, 1, 65</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>is that a t. of moys?</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 4.4.23" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 4, 23</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>